Ready_to_Upload:
You are now ready to upload your Instagram photos. On the next few pages, you will asked a few questions be shown instructions on how to upload your Instagram photos. You will be asked to repeat these steps for all 30 of your images. If you experience any technical difficulties or have any questions, please email the experimenter at: farerilab@gmail.com.

As a reminder, you are asked to provide 30-35 photos from your Instagram account that meet the following criteria:



Your photos should meet the following criteria:



1) They are photos that you've already posted to your Instagram account; please blur out/crop out your personal instagram handle.

2) They evoke positive feelings only

3) They are original photos posted by you (not re-posts, memes, or quotes originally posted by someone else)

4) They do not contain any inappropriate or illegal content (revealing clothing, nudity, drug paraphernalia, expletives, or politically charged content, bullying or other types of offensive material)

5) They are photos and not screenshots of videos

6) Of the 30-35 photos, please have at least 5 photos that include yourself

7) They are not from a business or professional account
8) Do not upload any duplicates of the same photo, each photo must be different. If duplicates are detected, you may be ineligible to participate in the study.

If you agree to abide by this criteria, please certify below and click the blue arrow to continue.

Step 5:
Step 5: Upload your image to the survey in the space provided. Please do not crop or edit your screenshot beyond hiding your username. We will take care of that for you.



You will also be asked to provide a brief, descriptive caption to go along with your photo so that when other participants view your photo they have some context. For example, if Doug the Pug submitted this photo, the caption may be, "lounging around in my crocs." 



  





Finally, you will also be asked to rate how the photo makes you feel.
